cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.MM

This paper deals with computer vision techniques for tracking densely-packed objects in a complex environment, which suggests a primary category of cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The use of machine learning models for object recognition and tracking also suggests sub-categories of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The application of these techniques to a physical system, specifically a honeybee hive, suggests a potential sub-category of cs.RO (Robotics and Control). Finally, the use of image recording and analysis techniques suggests a potential sub-category of cs.MM (Multimedia).
